\section*{Reproducibility and audit ledger}
\phantomsection\label{sec:reproducibility-main2}

\newcommand{\artifactcommit}{5de157b73409790b48e31972eaf3caf04dfe4c9a}
\newcommand{\artifacttag}{v1.0.0}
\newcommand{\artifactdoi}{10.5281/zenodo.17565290}

All results in this paper are reproducible from the frozen artifact
\texttt{\artifactcommit} (tag \texttt{\artifacttag}), archived at DOI
\texttt{\artifactdoi}. The repository root includes a canonical checksum ledger
\texttt{SHA256SUMS.txt} containing relative paths and SHA-256 digests for
every file used in analysis and figure generation.


\medskip
\noindent\textbf{Reproduction checklist}
\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=1.2em]
\item \textbf{Commit}: \artifactcommit\ (tag \artifacttag)
\item \textbf{Checksum ledger}: \texttt{SHA256SUMS.txt} (one line per file; SHA-256)
\item \textbf{Parameter ledger}: \texttt{parameters.json}
\item \textbf{End-to-end scripts}: \texttt{run\_analysis.py}, \texttt{cce\_universal.py}
\item \textbf{Manifests and results}: \texttt{equivalence\_manifest.txt}, \texttt{substrate\_equivalence\_results.json}, \texttt{nine\_laws\_results.json}
\item \textbf{Figures}: \texttt{fig1\_gamma\_recovery.jpeg}–\texttt{fig5\_bsc\_contraction.jpeg}
\end{itemize}

